# UI Improvements & Screen Dimmer Plan

## Context

Single-screen Expo radio app. Layout: Header → ControlPanel → CategoryTabs → StationList.
Playback via `useRadioPlayer()` / `RadioPlayerService`. Hook signal: `playerState.isPlaying`.
`expo-keep-awake` already active while playing. No dimming logic exists yet.

## UI Improvement 1: Pinned Mini Player Bar

**Problem:** ControlPanel scrolls off-screen when browsing the station list.

**Implementation:**
- Add `components/MiniPlayerBar.tsx` — fixed to bottom, visible when `currentStation` is set
- Show: station name, play/pause, stop (reuse `togglePlayPause`, `stop` from App.tsx)
- Respect bottom safe area inset (home indicator on iOS)
- Optional later: expandable volume or dim-mode indicator

**Files:** `components/MiniPlayerBar.tsx` (new), `App.tsx` (wire up)

## UI Improvement 2: Finish i18n in ControlPanel ✅ DONE

**Problem:** ControlPanel uses hardcoded Korean (`연결 중...`, `볼륨`) while other components use `useLanguage()`.

**Completed:**
- `useLanguage()` wired into `ControlPanel.tsx`
- Loading and volume labels use `t.loading`, `t.volume`
- Play/pause/stop buttons use `t.play`, `t.pause`, `t.stop` as accessibility labels

**Follow-up (optional):** Map `RadioPlayerService` error messages through i18n in the UI layer

## Feature: Screen Dim to ~70% After 1 Minute

**Goal:** After 1 continuous minute of playback, dim screen to ~70% brightness. Audio continues. Tap restores brightness and resets timer.

**Approach:** In-app overlay (preferred over `expo-brightness`)
- Full-screen `View` with `backgroundColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.3)'` (~70% perceived brightness)
- Does not alter system brightness; works consistently on iOS and Android
- Keep `PlayerKeepAwake` — dimming and keep-awake coexist

**Hook: `hooks/useScreenDimmer.ts`**
- Watch `playerState.isPlaying`
- Start 1-min timer when `isPlaying` becomes true (not during `isLoading`)
- Set `isDimmed = true` after timeout
- Clear timer + remove overlay on pause, stop, or station change
- Tap → `isDimmed = false`, restart timer if still playing
- `__DEV__` override: optional 10s timer for testing

**Component: `components/ScreenDimOverlay.tsx`**
- Absolute positioned, high zIndex, tappable to wake
- Optional hint text via i18n (`screenDimmedHint`)

**Integration in `App.tsx`:**
```tsx
const { isDimmed, wake } = useScreenDimmer(playerState);
// ...
<ScreenDimOverlay visible={isDimmed} onPress={wake} />
```

## Behavior Matrix

| Event | Action |
|-------|--------|
| `isPlaying` → true | Start 1-min timer |
| Timer fires | Show dim overlay |
| User taps | Hide overlay, restart timer if playing |
| Pause / Stop | Clear timer, remove overlay |
| Station switch while playing | Reset timer |
| App backgrounded | Clear overlay (restore on foreground if still playing) |

## Implementation Order

1. ~~i18n in ControlPanel~~ ✅ Done
2. MiniPlayerBar (~1–2 hrs) — **next**
3. useScreenDimmer + ScreenDimOverlay (~1–2 hrs)

## Out of Scope (Future)

- Centralized theme / dark mode
- Lock-screen now playing controls
- User-configurable dim delay
- System brightness via `expo-brightness`
